    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="367"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/15133½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Thank you for letting me see
                    these papers.<note n="5" xml:id="d367fn1">The papers referred to cannot be
                        identified.</note> I am entirely open to anything that events may open to
                    us, even the recognition of Carranza if he should develop the necessary
                    influence and begin to bring real order out of chaos. But I think our statement
                    ought to precipitate things (in the chemical sense) and open up either this or
                    some other channel of action.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
